<title>INDIA: India approves investment in Haldia expansion.</title>
<headline>India approves investment in Haldia expansion.</headline>
<dateline>NEW DELHI 1996-10-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Indian Industry Ministry said on Friday that it approved foreign direct investment of 4.35 billion rupees to expand a cracker plant owned by Haldia Petrochemicals Ltd in the eastern state of West Bengal.  </p>
<p>The ministry said in a statement that Haldia planned to raise the cracker's annual capacity to 420,000 tonnes from 300,000.</p>
<p>The capacity could be further increased to 476,000 tonnes, the statement said.</p>
<p>The government of West Bengal is the main promoter of Haldia Petrochemicals Ltd.</p>
<p>--New Delhi newsroom +91-11 301 2024</p>
